    },
    {
      "id": "legend",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## NASA Apollo materials\n\nThe Apollo subset of the collection comes from the AARO-curated re-release of NASA materials, plus the original Apollo Image Library frames.\n\nKey finding: ==nearly every notable observation in the Apollo transcripts is identified by the crew or Capcom in real time== as a known cause (S-IVB debris, cosmic ray phosphenes, EMI). The single unresolved item is the Schmitt lunar surface flash near Grimaldi, which is consistent with a small meteoroid impact (modern TLP literature).\n\nThis canvas groups the materials by source, witness, and identified cause.",
      "x": -1100,
      "y": -500,
      "width": 650,
      "height": 480,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "src-d1",
