    {
      "id": "resolved",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Resolved in source\n\n==Fragment field== (Apollo 17): identified by crew as S-IVB debris\n\n==Rotating bright objects== (Apollo 17, 10-12 Earth diameters): identified by LMP Schmitt as S-IVB engine bell + SLA panels\n\n==Bright flashes between the eyes== (Apollo 17): cosmic ray phosphenes\n\n==Particles of light==, dark quadrant 1 (Apollo 12): attributed by LMP Bean to water boiler discharge\n\n==All-8's flash on AGS== (Apollo 12): Capcom identifies as Bethpage-known EMI\n\n==LM tracking light==: visible non-detection issue, not a hardware failure",
      "x": 800,
      "y": 50,
      "width": 500,
      "height": 540,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "unresolved",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Unresolved (genuinely open)\n\n==Grimaldi lunar surface flash== (Apollo 17, Schmitt): brief flash on lunar surface north of Grimaldi crater. Schmitt himself proposed meteoroid impact hypothesis and suggested seismometer cross-check. Whether the contemporaneous seismometer record contains a corresponding event is not in this collection.\n\nThis is the only Apollo observation in the collection without an in-document resolution.",
      "x": 800,
      "y": 650,
      "width": 500,
      "height": 380,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "inc-rotating",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "02 - Incidents/Incident - 1972 Apollo 17 Rotating Bright Object.md",
      "x": -700,
      "y": 1210,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "color": "5"
    }
